Definition: active AD 250-500) who discussed the Mishnaic law in the law schools of Palestine and Mesopotamia where they explained and applied earlier teachings and whose discussions are recorded in the Talmud
Example: they emphasized the study of Torah and the importance of personal action and the fulfillment of the commandments
Synonyms: rabbi, one, of, a, group, rabbis, active, AD, -, who, discussed, the, Mishnaic, law, in, schools, Palestine, and, Mesopotamia, where, they, explained, applied, earlier, teachings, whose, discussions, are, recorded, Talmud, emphasized, study, Torah, importance, personal, action, fulfillment, commandments
Category: noun.person
